3. How driver.getTitle() method works internally?
driver.getTitle() --> Title of the WebPage and it will return the String
This will return the GET API call
https://www.w3.org/TR/webdriver/#get-title -> URL
GET	/session/{session id}/title
This command returns the document title of session's current top-level browsing context, equivalent to calling document.title.
Let title be the session's current top-level browsing context's active document's title.
Title will be present always from HEAD tag in the Html DOM
String getTitle() --> this is present in the WebDriver interface
Implementation is available in execute() method
execute() --> this is available in the RemoteWebDriver class

